SENATE CHAMBER
STATE OF OKLAHOMA DISPOSITION
FLOOR AMENDMENT No. ________
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
(Date)
I move to amend House Bill No. 1462 on Page 39, Lines 14 through 16, by deleting all new
language and inserting the following new language:
“Before acceptance of a payment toward fines, fees, or assessments, the court clerk shall inquire of
the offender whether restitution is owed on the case. If the court has ordered restitution, the court
clerk shall inform the offender that payment of such restitution shall be prioritized over payment of
fines, fees, or assessments.”
